description:
&lt;p&gt;Frimley Health is a leading innovative NHS Foundation Trust, providing hospital services for 900,000 people across Berkshire, Hampshire, Surrey and South Buckinghamshire delivered on three main sites.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our new Emergency Assessment Centre on the Wexham Park Hospital site will be fully open early April 2019 and brings together a large, state-of-the-art Emergency Department, Ambulatory Emergency Care Unit with an impressive 30 treatment spaces, a multi-specialty assessment ward and Acute Medical and Surgical short stay units. With integrated Radiology providing CT, X-Ray and Ultrasound located within the assessment centre, this provides a modern working environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are opportunities to join Frimley Health NHS Foundation Trust providing both acute medical services and medical speciality in-reach.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are interested in applications from Consultants and specialist trainees within 6 months of their CCT in multiple specialities. We are specifically interested in applications for the following however specialities may be considered&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Consultants in Older Persons Medicine &amp; Frailty&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post supports the Trusts’ plans to improve the management of the emergency medical take. The posts are full time, although candidates unable to work full-time are also invited to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameDr Lucy AbbottAdditional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more information or to arrange an informal visit please contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dr Gareth Roberts, Deputy Chief of Service for Medicine. Tel: (01753) 633388&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mrs Kirstin MacDonald Associate Director, Medicine &amp; Emergency Services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tel: (01753) 633388&lt;/p&gt;
